segment.source: The following tables show the supported language packs and language interface packs (LIPs) for Windows 10, Windows Server 2016 Technical Preview, and Windows Server 2012 R2.
segment.target: The following tables show the supported language packs and language interface packs (LIPs) for Windows 10, Windows Server 2016 Technical Preview, and Windows Server 2012 R2.

segment.source: Corporations and users can download LIPs from the Microsoft.com web site and add them to any genuine copy of Windows that has the supported parent language installed.
segment.target: Corporations and users can download LIPs from the Microsoft.com web site and add them to any genuine copy of Windows that has the supported parent language installed.

segment.source: For more information or to download a LIP, see Local Language Program.
segment.target: For more information or to download a LIP, see Local Language Program.

segment.source: LIPs must be installed to the operating system that they support.
segment.target: LIPs must be installed to the operating system that they support.

segment.source: Windows 10 LIPs cannot be used on Windows 8.1; similarly, Windows 8.1 LIPs cannot be used on Windows 10.
segment.target: Windows 10 LIPs cannot be used on Windows 8.1; similarly, Windows 8.1 LIPs cannot be used on Windows 10.

segment.source: OEMs and system builders with Microsoft Software License Terms can get the LIPs from the Microsoft OEM site and OEM Partner Center.
segment.target: OEMs and system builders with Microsoft Software License Terms can get the LIPs from the Microsoft OEM site and OEM Partner Center.

segment.source: For a complete list of supported languages and locales, see Locale Identifier Constants and Strings.
segment.target: For a complete list of supported languages and locales, see Locale Identifier Constants and Strings.

segment.source: To learn more, see Add Language Packs to Windows.
segment.target: To learn more, see Add Language Packs to Windows.
